Germany,[d] officially the Federal Republic of Germany,[e] is a country
in Central Europe. It lies between the Baltic Sea and the North Sea to
the north and the Alps to the south. Its sixteen constituent states have
a total population of over 82 million in an area of 357,596 km2
(138,069 sq mi), making it the most populous member state of the
European Union. It borders Denmark to the north, Poland and the Czech
Republic to the east, Austria and Switzerland to the south, and France.